      • getDeclaredDataStructures

        public java.util.Set<DataStructure> getDeclaredDataStructures()
        Returns:
        All DataStructures that are explicitly declared in the model. Some DataStructures may not be explicitly declared. For example, in MML code one can use x:t in the RHS of an equation. This can instantiate a variable in the model called "x:t" without an explicit declaration.
